<h1 id = "Apollo_1_0-SNAPSHOT">Apollo 1.0-SNAPSHOT</h1>

<h1 id = "_project_slogan_">{project_slogan}</h1>
          <div></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div id="content">
      <div class="wrapper">
<p><a href="http://activemq.apache.org/apollo/">Apollo</a> is a 
<a href="http://www.scala-lang.org">Scala 2.8</a> based messaging broker. 
It can be thought of as a forked and stripped down version of 
<a href="http://activemq.apache.org/">Apache ActiveMQ</a> . It is focused on 
providing a simple, stable, scalable messaging core which is easy to extend.</p>

<h2 id = "Implemented_Features">Implemented Features</h2>

<ul>
<li><a href="documentation/user-manual.html#Destination&#95;Types">Topics and Queues</a></li>
<li>Queue Browsers</li>
<li><a href="documentation/user-manual.html#Topic&#95;Durable&#95;Subscriptions">Durable Subscriptions on Topics</a></li>
<li><a href="documentation/user-manual.html#Reliable&#95;Messaging">Persistence</a></li>
<li>Message swapping</li>
<li><a href="documentation/user-manual.html#Message&#95;Selectors">Message Selectors</a></li>
<li>ACL based security</li>
<li>JAAS Authorization</li>
<li>SSL/TLS Support</li>
<li>REST based management</li>
<li><a href="http://stomp.github.com/stomp-specification-1.0.html">Stomp 1.0</a> Protocol
Support</li>
<li><a href="http://stomp.github.com/stomp-specification-1.1.html">Stomp 1.1</a> Protocol
Support</li>
</ul>

